<subSubSection id="C3246572FFEDC942FF62FF1CFE04FE6E" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFEDC942FF62FF1CFC66FE4A" blockId="76.[151,1437,150,465]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFEDC942FF62FF1CFDCDFF73" bold="true" box="[199,579,150,177]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
Description. Female (
<typeStatus id="5485885BFFEDC942FE6DFF1CFDB8FF73" box="[456,566,150,176]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 18.8. Prosoma 6.9 long, 6.2 wide. Opisthosoma 11.5 long, 7.3 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.50, 0.40, 0.33, 0.37; interdistances: 0.40, 0.24, 0.65, 0.70, 0.35, 0.25. Legs: I: 26.8 (7.7, 3.2, 7.0, 7.1, 1.8); II: 28.6 (8.3, 3.5, 7.5, 7.4, 1.9); III: 19.6 (6.4, 2.7, 4.9, 4.7, 1.6); IV: 24.0 (7.5, 2.6, 6.0, 6.0, 1.9). Spination follows the generic pattern except metatarsus IV: r1-1-2. Epigyne: EF wider than long; MAB present, embedded in epigynal field; MS longer than wide, roughly drop-shaped; EP roughly as long as wide with lateral margins extending posteriorly to lateral margins of MS (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFEDC942FCA2FEC1FCE6FEA6" box="[775,872,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 309–311" captionStartId="75.[151,264,1172,1196]" captionTargetBox="[177,1410,642,1141]" captionTargetId="figure-185@75.[170,1418,633,1148]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURES 309–311. Meri zeteki spec. nov. female (MCZ 99617, holotype) (309 epigyne, 310 vulva, 311 schematic course of internal duct system). ag—anterior groove; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP— glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550416" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550416/files/figure.png" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Fig. 309</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFEDC942FCD7FEC1FC2EFEA6" box="[882,928,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 313–314" captionStartId="75.[151,264,2009,2033]" captionTargetBox="[178,1383,1316,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-232@75.[178,1410,1292,1986]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURES 313–314. Meri zeteki spec. nov. female (MCZ 99617, holotype) (313 epigyne, 314 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550420/files/figure.png" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">313</figureCitation>
). Vulva: GP longer than wide, antero-mediad; SP elongate with few surface folds; FD antero-mediad (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFEDC942FCA3FEE5FC2CFE4A" box="[774,930,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 309–311" captionStartId="75.[151,264,1172,1196]" captionTargetBox="[177,1410,642,1141]" captionTargetId="figure-185@75.[170,1418,633,1148]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURES 309–311. Meri zeteki spec. nov. female (MCZ 99617, holotype) (309 epigyne, 310 vulva, 311 schematic course of internal duct system). ag—anterior groove; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP— glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550416" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550416/files/figure.png" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Figs 310–311</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFEDC942FC0BFEE5FC52FE4A" box="[942,988,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 313–314" captionStartId="75.[151,264,2009,2033]" captionTargetBox="[178,1383,1316,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-232@75.[178,1410,1292,1986]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURES 313–314. Meri zeteki spec. nov. female (MCZ 99617, holotype) (313 epigyne, 314 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550420/files/figure.png" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">314</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFEDC942FF62FE19FE04FE6E" blockId="76.[151,1437,150,465]" box="[199,394,403,429]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
